/u/Salsh_Loli on TIL The painter of Madame Rimsky-Korsakov Portrait, Franz Winterhalter, was well known for painting Queen Victoria and Empress Sisi, two most beautiful women in their time
While it's true that the human body and facial characteristics change for every 100 years, i doubt people today would look that different from 100 or 200 years ago. It's hard to envision how people from decades ago would look different compare to modern time mostly because of different hairstyles and clothing. In vintage photos, people dressed up what is contemporary, but there are rare cases where some look particularly modern. Here are some interesting examples: https://cdn.theatlantic.com/assets/media/img/photo/2012/02/the-civil-war-part-2-the-people/c29_77457818/main_1200.jpg?1420517524 (this was Lewis Powell who was executed in 1864 for assassination attempt) https://cdn.theatlantic.com/assets/media/img/photo/2012/02/the-civil-war-part-2-the-people/c46_0004208a/main_1200.jpg?1420517533 https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Sadness%2C_by_Julia_Margaret_Cameron.jpg/220px-Sadness%2C_by_Julia_Margaret_Cameron.jpg Regarding the painting, i am seriously in love with her hair.   